examples.en: Asthma has gripped me by the throat.
She gripped on to the railings with both hands.
The scandal has gripped the nation.
The hawk gripped the mouse in its talons.
I gripped the door handle and pulled as hard as I could.
He held his weapon gripped between his knees.
Steve gripped the steering wheel tightly with both hands.
The little boy gripped his mother's hand tightly.
The entire city has been gripped by baseball mania.
Panic suddenly gripped me when it was my turn to speak.
A sense of impending doom (=coming very soon) gripped her.
She fell back in the chair and gripped her hands round the arms of it.
Since the General's death, the population has been gripped by mass hysteria.
